~ Flexible ‘Commercial’ zoning providing a wide variety of development opportunities
~ A generous 14,600sqm* site with a wide frontage of 146 metres
~ High exposure site with up to 40,000 passing vehicles per day
~ Second street frontage to Carlisle Place with right in right out access
~ This site has been held under the same ownership and operated as a successful car dealership for over 30 years

This high exposure site offers a broad range of alternate complying land uses and presents an ideal re-development opportunity. The development plan provides complying land uses such as: consulting rooms, bulky goods outlet, petrol filling station, shops, office, service trade premises (amongst others).

Ability to capture CBD outbound traffic prior to reaching the Tea Tree Plaza precinct and before the Golden Grove ‘McIntyre Road’ turn-off.

North East Road continues to be a prize car dealership corridor benefiting from high levels of passing traffic.  

Vendor open to Joint Venture and Leasing Enquiries

For Sale by Expressions of Interest closing Thursday 10th May 2018 at 4pm (ACST)

*approx.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: CAR DEALERSHIP OR PRIME DEVELOPMENT SITE
